languages.en: The One Where It All Began (Pilot)

languages.ko:
얘기할 것도 없어
같이 일하는 동료일 뿐야

languages.en:
There's nothing to tell.
It's just some guy I work with.
You're going out with the guy.

languages.ko:
남자랑 데이트하는 거잖아

There has to be something
wrong with him.

languages.ko:
등에 혹이라도 난 거야?

languages.en:
All right, Joey.
Be nice.

So does he have a hump

Wait, does he eat chalk?

I don't want her to go through

Okay, everybody relax.
This is not even a date.

두 사람이 함께 식사를 하고

languages.en:
It's just two people going out

Sounds like a date to me.

I'm in high school,

...and I realize l' m totally naked.

languages.ko:
그런데 아래를 내려다보니까

languages.en:
Then I look down and I realize
there is a phone...
...there.

-lnstead of--
-That's right!
Never had that one.

All of a sudden,
the phone starts to ring.

languages.ko:

languages.en:
What do I do?
Everyone starts looking at me.
They weren't looking at you before?

Finally, I figure
I'd better answer it.
And it turns out it's my mother.

languages.ko:
그게 정말 이상하단 얘기야

languages.en:
Which is very, very weird

Hi.

He says, " Hello, "
I want to kill myself.

I feel like someone pulled my
intestine out of my mouth...

누군가 내 목에 손을 집어넣고

languages.en:
-...and tied it around my neck.
-Cookie?
Carol moved her stuff out today.

-Let me get you some coffee.
-Thanks.

No, don't!
Stop cleansing my aura.

그만, 내 기를 청소할

languages.en:
-Just leave my aura alone, okay?
-Fine, be murky.

languages.ko:
난 괜찮아, 솔직히

languages.en:
-I'll be fine. I hope she'll be happy.
-No, you don't.

languages.ko:
당연히 거짓말이지

languages.en:
No, I don't.
T o hell with her. She left me!
You never knew she was a lesbian?
No! Okay?

Why does everyone
keep fixating on that?

She didn't know.
How should I know?
Sometimes I wish I was a lesbian.
Did I say that out loud?

I told Mom and Dad last night.
They took it pretty well.

그래? 그럼 새벽 3시의

이제 손자 보긴 글렀다고

... " I'll never have grandchildren, "

Sorry.

Look, you' re feeling

languages.ko:
지금 많이 고통스러울 거야

languages.en:
You' re angry.
You' re hurting.

languages.ko: 이럴 때 해답이 뭔 줄 알아?

languages.en:
Can I tell you what

Strip joints!

Hey, you're single.

난 독신이 싫단 말야, 알아?

-Rachel?
-Oh, Monica! Thank God!

커다란 망치를 든 남자가

...and a guy with a hammer

얘들아, 여긴 레이첼이야

Everybody, this is Rachel,

This is everybody.
Chandler and Phoebe...

지금 말할 거야, 아님

Well, it started about

I was in the room

...and I was looking at this
really gorgeous Limoges gravy boat.

엄청나게 큰 수프 그릇이

languages.en: When all of a sudden--
Sweet ' N Low?

배리보다 그 수프 그릇에

I got freaked out,

그러더니 갑자기 정신이 번쩍

How much Barry looks

배리가 감자 머리 아저씨처럼

I always knew

I had to get out of there,

"내가 왜, 누굴 위해서

languages.en:
... "Why am I doing this, "

어쨌든, 그런데 어디로

I didn't know where to go,

languages.ko:
너랑은 연락 안 한 지

... but you' re the only person

이 도시에 사는 사람은

근데 난 결혼식에 초대도

저 남자가 여자한테

I guess he bought her the pipe organ,

"T una or egg salad!
Decide! "

"I'll have whatever
Christina's having. "

I can't marry him.

languages.ko:
아빠, 죄송해요

languages.en:
I' m sorry.
I just don't love him.
Well, it matters to me!

" If I let go of my hair,
my head will fall off. "

She should not be
wearing those pants.
Push her down the stairs!

Push her!
Push her down the stairs!
Come on, Daddy, listen!

languages.ko:
평생을 사는 동안 다들 저한테

languages.en:
All my life, everyone's
always told me, "You're a shoe! "
"You' re a shoe! "

languages.ko:
그런데 갑자기 제가 생각하죠
신발이 되기 싫다면?

languages.en: What if I don't want to be a shoe?
What if I want to be a purse?

languages.ko:
지갑이 되고 싶다면?
아님, 모자가 되고 싶다면?

languages.en: Or a hat?

No, I don't want you
to buy me a hat!

languages.ko:
모자를 사달란 얘기가 아녜요

languages.en: It's a metaphor, Daddy!
You can see where he'd have trouble.

Look, Daddy,
it's my life.

Well, maybe I'll just stay
here with Monica.

languages.ko:
모니카랑 여기 있기로

languages.en:
I guess we've established

Well, maybe that's my decision.

languages.ko:
어쩌면 아빠 돈은

languages.en: Maybe I don't need your money.

Wait!
I said maybe!
Just breathe. That's it.
T ry to think of nice, calm things.

Raindrops on roses
And whiskers on kittens

Doorbells and sleigh bells
And something with mittens

languages.en:
La la la something
And noodles with string
I' m all better now.
I helped.
This is probably for the best.

languages.ko:
독립해서 네 인생을

languages.en:
Independence. Controlling your life.
The whole hat thing.
You can always come to Joey.

필요한 게 있으면

Me and Chandler live across the hall.

Stop hitting on her!

languages.en: Like there's a rule, or something?
I got it.

Please don't do that again.
It's a horrible sound.
It's Paul.

Oh, God, is it 6:30?
Buzz him in.

-Who's Paul?
-Paul, the wine guy?
Maybe.

잠깐, 와인 담당 폴이랑

languages.en:
Your " not a real date"

- 레이첼, 취소하라면 할게

languages.en:
-Rach, I can cancel.
-Please, go, I'll be fine.

Ross, are you okay?

languages.ko:
와인 파는 사람?

languages.en: Or he just complains a lot?

Hi, come in!
Paul, this is...

...everybody.
Everybody, this is Paul.

-The wine guy.
-I didn't catch your name. Paul?

미안하지만 이름을 못 들었는데

languages.en:
I'll be right back.
I've just gotta go--

Change.

Sit down.

속눈썹을 네 개나 뽑았어

I just pulled out four eyelashes.

Hey, Paul, here's a tip.

languages.ko:
모니카는 목을 계속

languages.en:
She really likes it when you

... until it starts to get red.
Shut up, Joey!
What are you up to tonight?

languages.ko:
아루바로 신혼여행 가려고
했었는데, 지금은 없어

languages.en:
I was supposed to be headed

...so, nothing.

Although, Aruba.
This time of year?
T alk about your...

If you don't want

조이랑 챈들러가 새 가구

...Joey and Chandler are

고맙지만 오늘은 나가서 좀

languages.en:
-It's been a long day.
-Oh, sure.
Pheebs, wanna help?

사랑은 뜨거운 여름비

Love is sweet as summer showers
Love is a wondrous work of art

고 놈이 당신 가슴을

Thank you.

작은 나사 한 뭉치를

little worm guys.

I have no bracket-y thing.

languages.en:
I would have to say

-I have no idea.

-All finished.
This was Carol's favorite beer.

languages.ko:
항상 캔으로 마셨지

languages.en:
She always drank it out of the can.

languages.ko:
너 술 주정 시작하면

languages.en:
-Start with that, we're out of here.

languages.en:
She got the furniture,
the stereo, the good TV.

-You guys.
-You got screwed.

-Oh, my God.
-I know. I' m such an idiot.

the dentist five times a week.

치과에 일주일에 너댓번 씩

languages.en: I mean, how clean can teeth get?
My brother's going through that.
How did you get over it?

languages.ko:
부인이 소중히 여기던 걸

languages.en:
He might accidentally
break something valuable of hers.

-Say her--
-Leg?

That's one way of doing it.
I went for the watch.
You actually broke her watch?

The worst I ever did was shred
my old boyfriend's favorite towel.

languages.ko:
그 남자의 수건을 갈가리

languages.en:
-Steer clear of you.
-That's right.

Barry, l' m sorry.
I am so sorry.

You probably think it's about making

languages.ko:
자기가 양말 신고 자는 걸

그게 아냐, 그런 게 아니고

languages.en:
It's about me.
And I just--

The machine cut me off again.
Anyway....

I know that some lucky girl is going

languages.ko:
당신 부인이 될 여자는
정말 행운이라는 거

languages.en:
But it isn't me.
It's not me.

languages.ko:
사실 난 지금 내가

languages.en:
Not that I have any idea who "me" is

I' m divorced.

-l' m only 26, and l' m divorced!
-Shut up!
That only took me an hour.

We haven't had a relationship

languages.ko:
조이와 나는 너처럼

languages.en:
You have had the love of a woman

친밀함을 4년이나 나누더니

languages.en:
Four years of closeness and sharing,
after which she ripped your heart out.

languages.ko: 그래서 우린 그 짓을 안 해

languages.en: That is why we don't do it!

나한테 맞는 여자가 하나

languages.en:
I mean, what if you get one

languages.en:
Unfortunately, in my case,

One woman.

나한테 맞는 아이스크림은

languages.en:
Let me tell you something.

Rocky road and cookie dough

You got married.

현실세계에 온 걸 환영한다

Welcome back to the world.
Grab a spoon!

languages.ko:
솔직히 배가 고픈 건지

languages.en:
-I don't know if I'm hungry or horny.
-Then stay out of my freezer.
Ever since she walked out on me....

You wanna spell it out with noodles?

아뇨, 이런 얘긴 다섯 번은

languages.en:
It's more of a fifth date

그럼 다섯 번째 데이트가

languages.en:
So there's going to be
a fifth date?
Isn't there?

Yeah, yeah.
I think there is.
What were you going to say?
Ever since she left me...

Oh, God!
I' m so sorry.

languages.ko:
물을 뿜으라고 한 얘기는

languages.en:
Being spit on is probably
not what you need right now.
How long?

-Two years.
-Wow.
I' m glad you smashed her watch.

So you still think you might
want that fifth date?

languages.ko:
우리 다섯 번째 데이트
할 수 있는 건가요?

languages.en:
Yeah.
Yeah, I do.

We are gathered here
to join Joanie Louise Cunningham...

...and Charles.
Chachi, Chachi, Chachi...
...in the bonds of holy matrimony.
See!

languages.ko:
저것 봐, 조니는 차치를 사랑해

languages.en:
